headline: 3 Apartment REITs to Buy Right Now
summary: Residential housing was often viewed as a safe haven during recessions, but the coronavirus pandemic has impacted residential rentals, particularly multifamily and apartment real estate investment trusts (REITs) in unexpected ways.  A move from urban city centers to suburban markets has shifted supply and demand in many markets, putting tremendous pressure on rents and landlords.  This, coupled with extended eviction moratoriums and a record number of tenants unable to pay rent, makes it a tough time to be an apartment REIT.
